

===Logic: Assigning an externally transmitted MIDI control message to a plug in or software instrument parameter.===


----


'''1.''' Open the plug in or software instrument.

'''2.''' Go to the top menu and go to '''Logic Pro/ Preferences / Automation'''

'''3.''' Click '''Learn message''' in the window that appears

'''4.''' Move the slider or knob on your MIDI controller than is transmitting the desired MIDI message you wish to assign.

'''5.''' Click the plug in or software instrument parameter you wish to affect. A new window titled "'''controller assignments'''" will appear. 

'''6.''' Move your MIDI controller fader/knob one more time. A dialog box might appear asking if you want to "'''reassign'''" the message. Click "'''reassign'''" and close the '''controller assignments''' window.


You should now be able to control the respective parameter via the control message assignment.



